line_1: Types of the nuptial tyes they celebrate:
line_2: While bells her ears with tongues discordant grate,

line_1: For tongue to speak, or verse to celebrate,
line_2: But, O my God, thy wonders are too great

line_1: Came there the nuptials to celebrate:
line_2: Some the near foe with brondir'n to amate;

line_1: Came there the nuptials to celebrate:
line_2: Me too they welcome to the hall of state;

line_1: Came there the nuptials to celebrate:
line_2: A round or two, and chuse me out a mate:
